01:16:39.000 --> 01:16:42.120
A Structure of Repeating Units.

01:16:42.120 --> 01:16:45.070
A lamp is a great gift, I think.

01:16:45.070 --> 01:16:49.560
The brass tack ouch of a hand
to a hot bulb takes you straight

01:16:49.560 --> 01:16:52.800
to the top of the threshold
of feeling.

01:16:52.800 --> 01:16:57.250
A small plastic object held to
the cheek is also quite nice.

01:16:57.250 --> 01:17:00.990
I love poly socks,
dishtowels with rick-rack,

01:17:00.990 --> 01:17:05.040
a surfboard anointed
with one aqua stripe.

01:17:05.040 --> 01:17:09.060
Idle want seems to dog me along
a long cord that's plugged

01:17:09.060 --> 01:17:12.860
into the boot in the mouth
of the near recent past.

01:17:12.860 --> 01:17:16.350
The plastic, we both know,
is nothing but a patchwork

01:17:16.350 --> 01:17:22.980
of particles, a mash-up of atoms,
petroleum before or after its oil

01:17:22.980 --> 01:17:26.720
but still, it means so much more.

01:17:26.720 --> 01:17:28.020
Something finer than fine.

01:17:28.020 --> 01:17:30.060
Like pearls bred from
time and insouciance.

01:17:30.060 --> 01:17:34.960
Or something like that.

01:17:34.960 --> 01:17:38.100
I turn out the light,
lock the door, lie down,

01:17:38.100 --> 01:17:41.950
brush my hair from my forehead,
and listen for the cinematographer

01:17:41.950 --> 01:17:46.740
